# CrystalAI — Master Context

This file is generated during setup. Copy from CLAUDE.md.template and customize.

## Plugin Paths
- **Plugin root:** ~/Documents/GitHub/CrystalAI/
- **Vault:** [set in crystal.local.yaml]
- **Config:** crystal.local.yaml (personal) + crystal.secrets.yaml (credential paths)

## Quick Start
1. Copy template files: `cp crystal.local.yaml.template crystal.local.yaml && cp crystal.secrets.yaml.template crystal.secrets.yaml`
2. Fill in your config values
3. Install: `claude plugin install --scope user ~/Documents/GitHub/CrystalAI`
4. Run `crystal:setup` to validate

## State Hierarchy
All agent state lives in `state/`:
- `environments/` — execution environments (servers, workstations)
- `integrations/` — external service references
- `entities/` — orgs, schools, people
- `behavioral/` — domain-grouped rules
- `patterns/` — copy-paste execution references
- `memory/` — general reference
- `operational/` — live state (logs, queues, manifests)
- `sessions/` — session logs
- `feedback/` — correction inbox (processed by /weekly into behavioral/)
- `glossary.md` — abbreviation decoder ring

## Skills
All skills are namespaced `crystal:*`. See skill directories for details.

